topic: Movie Workflow Series ("The Batman movies explorative search")

goals.1: Investigate the works (aka derivative works) related to the Batman and individuate the movies. Return the movies along with the year of production and the director.
goals.2: Return the main Batman movie series produced in the last four decades and compare them in terms of length, number of actors involved and costs.
goals.3: Investigate what are the workers (writers, actors, etc.) who had a role in more Batman movies so far.
goals.4: Compare the ratings of the single movies and of the series. Indentify the movie with highest rating from the critics and the "best" series overall
goals.5: Return how many actors who are members of the cast of the "Dark Knight Trilogy" by Christopher Nolan have [Kavin Bacon number](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Six_Degrees_of_Kevin_Bacon#:~:text=Kevin%20Bacon%20himself%20has%20a,Bacon%20number%20is%20N%2B1.) equal to 2

name: workflow5_1

1.narrative:
startup the evaluation
setup the file and create the empty json
show all the derivative works related to the batman
find the instances of this derivative works
1.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?inst ?iName WHERE { wd:Q2695156 wdt:P4969 ?obj . ?obj wdt:P31 ?inst. ?inst <http://schema.org/name> ?iName . }
SELECT DISTINCT ?film ?name WHERE { wd:Q2695156 wdt:P4969 ?film . ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424. ?film <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }
SELECT DISTINCT ?prop ?name WHERE { wd:Q2695156 wdt:P4969 ?film . ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424; ?prop ?o. ?prop sc:name ?name. FILTER(isLiteral(?o)). } ORDER BY DESC (?name)
output: The Encyclopedia of Science Fiction ID
Museum of Modern Art work ID
Box Office Mojo film ID (former scheme)
BFI Films, TV and people ID
AFI Catalog of Feature Films ID

1.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?film ?name ?date WHERE { wd:Q2695156 wdt:P4969 ?film . ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424; wdt:P2754 ?date. ?film sc:name ?name. }
SELECT DISTINCT ?film ?name ?date WHERE { wd:Q2695156 wdt:P4969 ?film . ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424; wdt:P577 ?date. ?film sc:name ?name. }

1.narrative: show the minimum year of publication (the first publication ever)
1.query: SELECT ?film ?name (year(xsd:dateTime(min(?date))) as ?year) WHERE { wd:Q2695156 wdt:P4969 ?film . ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424; wdt:P577 ?date. ?film sc:name ?name. } GROUP BY ?film ?name
SELECT DISTINCT ?prop ?name WHERE { wd:Q2695156 wdt:P4969 ?film . ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424; ?prop ?obj. ?prop sc:name ?name. FILTER(REGEX(?name,"director")). }

SELECT ?name (year(xsd:dateTime(min(?date))) as ?year) ?director WHERE { wd:Q2695156 wdt:P4969 ?film . ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424; wdt:P57 ?dir; wdt:P577 ?date. ?film sc:name ?name. ?dir sc:name ?director. }

1.narrative: show all together with the respective URI for the films and the directors, for evaluation purpose
1.query: SELECT ?film ?name ?dir ?director (year(xsd:dateTime(min(?date))) as ?year) WHERE { wd:Q2695156 wdt:P4969 ?film . ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424; wdt:P57 ?dir; wdt:P577 ?date. ?film sc:name ?name. ?dir sc:name ?director. }

2.narrative:
more elements mixed between URI and literals
add the year element
add the director element
find something that tells me that a film is part of a series
2.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?prop ?name WHERE { wd:Q2695156 wdt:P4969 ?film . ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424. ?film ?prop ?series. ?prop <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }
output: Box Office Mojo film ID (former scheme)
AFI Catalog of Feature Films ID
original language of film or TV show
BFI Films, TV and people ID
The Encyclopedia of Science Fiction ID
contributor to the creative work or subject
Museum of Modern Art work ID

2.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?series ?name WHERE { wd:Q2695156 wdt:P4969 ?film . ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424. ?film wdt:P179 ?series. ?series <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }

2.narrative: find the date of production or publication
2.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?prop ?name WHERE { wd:Q2695156 wdt:P4969 ?film . ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424. ?film wdt:P179 ?series. ?series ?prop ?o. ?prop sc:name ?name. }
output: original language of film or TV show
The Encyclopedia of Science Fiction ID
Box Office Mojo franchise ID (former scheme)

2.narrative: show publication date and start time
2.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?series ?name ?date ?start WHERE { wd:Q2695156 wdt:P4969 ?film . ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424. ?film wdt:P179 ?series. OPTIONAL{?series wdt:P577 ?date.} OPTIONAL{?series wdt:P580 ?start.} ?series sc:name ?name. }

2.narrative: show publication date and start time
2.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?series ?name ?date ?start WHERE { wd:Q2695156 wdt:P4969 ?film . ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424. ?film wdt:P179 ?series. ?series wdt:P577 ?date. BIND(year(xsd:dateTime(?date)) AS ?year). FILTER(?year > 1982). ?series sc:name ?name. }

2.narrative: show all together filtering for series of the last 4 decades
2.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?series ?name (COUNT(DISTINCT ?film) AS ?num_film) (COUNT(DISTINCT ?cast) AS ?actors) (sum(?duration) AS ?tot_len) (sum(?cost) AS ?tot_cost) WHERE { wd:Q2695156 wdt:P4969 ?film . ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424. ?film wdt:P179 ?series. ?series wdt:P577 ?date. BIND(year(xsd:dateTime(?date)) AS ?year). FILTER(?year > 1982). ?film wdt:P161 ?cast; wdt:P2047 ?duration; wdt:P2130 ?cost. ?series sc:name ?name. } GROUP BY ?series ?name

3.narrative:
more literals associated to the same element
show the workers who worked on more films
3.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?worker ?name (COUNT(DISTINCT ?film) AS ?films) WHERE { wd:Q2695156 wdt:P4969 ?film . ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424. ?film ?prop ?worker. ?worker wdt:P31 wd:Q5. ?worker sc:name ?name. } GROUP BY ?worker ?name ORDER BY DESC (?films) LIMIT 10

4.narrative:
single literal associated to an URI
This query in the endpoint of wikidata returns exactly what we want, but here data is missing
4.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?prop ?pName WHERE { ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424. ?film ?prop ?obj. ?prop sc:name ?pName. FILTER(REGEX(?pName,"score")). }

4.narrative: This query in the endpoint of wikidata returns exactly what we want, but here data is missing
4.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?film ?obj WHERE { wd:Q2695156 wdt:P4969 ?film . ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424. ?film wdt:P444 ?obj. }

5.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?person ?personName WHERE { ?person wdt:P31 wd:Q5 . ?person <http://schema.org/name> ?personName . FILTER EXISTS{ ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424 ; wdt:P161 ?person . } FILTER(REGEX(?personName, "Bacon")) }

5.narrative: actors of Dark Knight Trilogy with Kevin Bacon equal to 2
5.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?actor ?actorName WHERE { wd:Q12859908 wdt:P527 ?f. ?f wdt:P161 ?actor . ?filmMiddle wdt:P161 ?actor ; wdt:P161 ?actorMiddle . ?film wdt:P161 ?actorMiddle ; wdt:P161 wd:Q3454165 . FILTER NOT EXISTS{ ?film3 wdt:P161 ?actor ; wdt:P161 wd:Q3454165 . } ?actor <http://schema.org/name> ?actorName . } LIMIT 100

5.narrative: number of actors of Dark Knight Trilogy with Kevin Bacon equal to 2
5.query: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT ?actor) AS ?bacon_2_actors WHERE { wd:Q12859908 wdt:P527 ?f. ?f wdt:P161 ?actor . ?filmMiddle wdt:P161 ?actor ; wdt:P161 ?actorMiddle . ?film wdt:P161 ?actorMiddle ; wdt:P161 wd:Q3454165 . FILTER NOT EXISTS{ ?film3 wdt:P161 ?actor ; wdt:P161 wd:Q3454165 . } ?actor <http://schema.org/name> ?actorName . }
